#compdef eskom-calendar
# ============================================================================
# eskom-calendar - South African loadshedding to iCalendar exporter (Rust, GPL-3.0)
#
# Author : Boyd Kane (beyarkay) + community contributors
# Upstream: https://github.com/beyarkay/eskom-calendar
#
# eskom-calendar parses Eskom and South African municipal loadshedding
# schedules (from PDFs, XLSX, HTML, CSV) into RFC 5545 iCalendar files,
# so users can subscribe to a per-suburb calendar feed and see exactly
# when their lights will go out. It is the project that powers
# `https://eskomcalendar.co.za` and the corresponding GitHub Releases of
# pre-generated .ics files.
#
# The RFC 5545 emission lane is built on the `icalendar` crate by
# hoodie (github.com/hoodie/icalendar), the canonical Rust library for
# constructing and serializing iCalendar VCALENDAR / VEVENT documents.
# It is declared at the top-level Cargo.toml:
#
#     icalendar = "0.15.4"
#
# and used verbatim in `src/main.rs`:
#
#     use icalendar::{Calendar, EventLike};
#
# A Calendar is built up by `.push()`-ing Event values, each Event is
# populated with `.summary()`, `.starts()`, `.ends()`, `.description()`,
# then the whole Calendar is rendered to RFC 5545 text by Display. The
# crate handles VCALENDAR / VEVENT framing, escaping, line folding at
# 75 octets, and DATE-TIME formatting per the spec.
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AXIS 196 :: iCALENDAR / RFC 5545 CALENDAR FORMAT
# Round 1286 :: Rust slot 1 of 4 :: OPENS Axis 196
#
# Cross-language canonical library family for this axis (proposed):
#   Rust    : icalendar          (hoodie/icalendar)         - RFC 5545 build/parse
#   Go      : arran4/golang-ical                            - RFC 5545 parse/serialize
#   TS/Node : ical.js            (kewisch/ical.js)          - RFC 5545 + jCal/jCard
#
# All three libraries center on the same RFC 5545 (iCalendar) and
# RFC 5546 (iTIP) text format - the same VCALENDAR / VEVENT / VTODO /
# VJOURNAL / VTIMEZONE component model, with the same RRULE recurrence
# semantics and the same property/parameter escaping rules - but ship
# from independent codebases. hoodie/icalendar in Rust is a clean-room
# builder API (Calendar / Event / Todo as Rust structs); arran4 in Go
# is a struct-tagged parser/emitter pair; ical.js comes out of the
# Mozilla Lightning calendar lineage (kewisch is ex-Mozilla Calendar)
# and is the most spec-complete of the three because it has to handle
# Thunderbird's calendar import quirks.
#
# eskom-calendar is the Rust opener - a real consumer that emits live
# .ics feeds at github.com/beyarkay/eskom-calendar/releases for many
# South African suburbs, exercised continuously by users subscribing
# their calendar apps to the GitHub-hosted URLs. It uses the icalendar
# crate to turn raw loadshedding rows into per-suburb VCALENDAR docs
# with one VEVENT per scheduled outage window.
# ============================================================================

_eskom-calendar() {
    local context state state_descr line
    typeset -A opt_args

    _arguments -s -S \
        '(-i --include-regex)'{-i,--include-regex}'[regex filter on input CSV schedule paths]:regex:' \
        '--output-ics-files[emit per-suburb .ics calendar files]:bool (default true):(true false)' \
        '--output-csv-file[emit consolidated machine-friendly CSV]:bool (default true):(true false)' \
        '--only-check-for-overlaps[fast YAML validity / overlap check; skip emission]:bool (default false):(true false)' \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[print help]' \
        '(- *)'{-V,--version}'[print version]'
}

_eskom-calendar "$@"
